static
3985 {
3986 /*the passstart values have 8 values: the 8th one indicates the byte after the end of the 7th (= last) pass*/
3987 unsigned i;
3988
3989 /*calculate width and height in pixels of each pass*/
3990 for(i = 0; i != 7; ++i) {
3991 passw[i] = (w + ADAM7_DX[i] - ADAM7_IX[i] - 1) / ADAM7_DX[i];
3992 passh[i] = (h + ADAM7_DY[i] - ADAM7_IY[i] - 1) / ADAM7_DY[i];
3993 if(passw[i] == 0) passh[i] = 0;
3994 if(passh[i] == 0) passw[i] = 0;
3995 }
3996
3997 filter_passstart[0] = padded_passstart[0] = passstart[0] = 0;
3998 for(i = 0; i != 7; ++i) {
3999 /*if passw[i] is 0, it's 0 bytes, not 1 (no filtertype-byte)*/
4000 filter_passstart[i + 1] = filter_passstart[i]
4001 + ((passw[i] && passh[i]) ? passh[i] * (1u + (passw[i] * bpp + 7u) / 8u) : 0);
4002 /*bits padded if needed to fill full byte at end of each scanline*/
4003 padded_passstart[i + 1] = padded_passstart[i] + passh[i] * ((passw[i] * bpp + 7u) / 8u);
4004 /*only padded at end of reduced image*/
4005 passstart[i + 1] = passstart[i] + (passh[i] * passw[i] * bpp + 7u) / 8u;
4006 }
4007}

static unsigned auto_choose_color ( LodePNGColorMode *  mode_out,

)

3883 {
3884 unsigned error = 0;
3885 unsigned palettebits;
3886 size_t i, n;
3887 size_t numpixels = stats->numpixels;
3888 unsigned palette_ok, gray_ok;
3889
3890 unsigned alpha = stats->alpha;
3891 unsigned key = stats->key;
3892 unsigned bits = stats->bits;
3893
3894 mode_out->key_defined = 0;
3895
3896 if(key && numpixels <= 16) {
3897 alpha = 1; /*too few pixels to justify tRNS chunk overhead*/
3898 key = 0;
3899 if(bits < 8) bits = 8; /*PNG has no alphachannel modes with less than 8-bit per channel*/
3900 }
3901
3902 gray_ok = !stats->colored;
3903 if(!stats->allow_greyscale) gray_ok = 0;
3904 if(!gray_ok && bits < 8) bits = 8;
3905
3906 n = stats->numcolors;
3907 palettebits = n <= 2 ? 1 : (n <= 4 ? 2 : (n <= 16 ? 4 : 8));
3908 palette_ok = n <= 256 && bits <= 8 && n != 0; /*n==0 means likely numcolors wasn't computed*/
3909 if(numpixels < n * 2) palette_ok = 0; /*don't add palette overhead if image has only a few pixels*/
3910 if(gray_ok && !alpha && bits <= palettebits) palette_ok = 0; /*gray is less overhead*/
3911 if(!stats->allow_palette) palette_ok = 0;
3912
3913 if(palette_ok) {
3914 const unsigned char* p = stats->palette;
3915 lodepng_palette_clear(mode_out); /*remove potential earlier palette*/
3916 for(i = 0; i != stats->numcolors; ++i) {
3917 error = lodepng_palette_add(mode_out, p[i * 4 + 0], p[i * 4 + 1], p[i * 4 + 2], p[i * 4 + 3]);
3918 if(error) break;
3919 }
3920
3921 mode_out->colortype = LCT_PALETTE;
3922 mode_out->bitdepth = palettebits;
3923
3924 if(mode_in->colortype == LCT_PALETTE && mode_in->palettesize >= mode_out->palettesize
3925 && mode_in->bitdepth == mode_out->bitdepth) {
3926 /*If input should have same palette colors, keep original to preserve its order and prevent conversion*/
3927 lodepng_color_mode_cleanup(mode_out);
3928 lodepng_color_mode_copy(mode_out, mode_in);
3929 }
3930 } else /*8-bit or 16-bit per channel*/ {
3931 mode_out->bitdepth = bits;
3932 mode_out->colortype = alpha ? (gray_ok ? LCT_GREY_ALPHA : LCT_RGBA)
3933 : (gray_ok ? LCT_GREY : LCT_RGB);
3934 if(key) {
3935 unsigned mask = (1u << mode_out->bitdepth) - 1u; /*stats always uses 16-bit, mask converts it*/
3936 mode_out->key_r = stats->key_r & mask;
3937 mode_out->key_g = stats->key_g & mask;
3938 mode_out->key_b = stats->key_b & mask;
3939 mode_out->key_defined = 1;
3940 }
3941 }
3942
3943 return error;

static void boundaryPM ( BPMLists *  lists,
BPMNode *  leaves,
size_t  numpresent,
int  c,
int  num 
)
static
941 {
942 unsigned lastindex = lists->chains1[c]->index;
943
944 if(c == 0) {
945 if(lastindex >= numpresent) return;
946 lists->chains0[c] = lists->chains1[c];
947 lists->chains1[c] = bpmnode_create(lists, leaves[lastindex].weight, lastindex + 1, 0);
948 } else {
949 /*sum of the weights of the head nodes of the previous lookahead chains.*/
950 int sum = lists->chains0[c - 1]->weight + lists->chains1[c - 1]->weight;
951 lists->chains0[c] = lists->chains1[c];
952 if(lastindex < numpresent && sum > leaves[lastindex].weight) {
953 lists->chains1[c] = bpmnode_create(lists, leaves[lastindex].weight, lastindex + 1, lists->chains1[c]->tail);
954 return;
955 }
956 lists->chains1[c] = bpmnode_create(lists, sum, lastindex, lists->chains1[c - 1]);
957 /*in the end we are only interested in the chain of the last list, so no
958 need to recurse if we're at the last one (this gives measurable speedup)*/
959 if(num + 1 < (int)(2 * numpresent - 2)) {
960 boundaryPM(lists, leaves, numpresent, c - 1, num);

962 }

◆ deflateDynamic()

static unsigned deflateDynamic ( LodePNGBitWriter *  writer,
Hash *  hash,
const unsigned char *  data,
size_t  datapos,
size_t  dataend,
const LodePNGCompressSettings *  settings,
unsigned  final 
)

1799 {
1800 unsigned error = 0;
1801
1802 /*
1803 A block is compressed as follows: The PNG data is lz77 encoded, resulting in
1804 literal bytes and length/distance pairs. This is then huffman compressed with
1805 two huffman trees. One huffman tree is used for the lit and len values ("ll"),
1806 another huffman tree is used for the dist values ("d"). These two trees are
1807 stored using their code lengths, and to compress even more these code lengths
1808 are also run-length encoded and huffman compressed. This gives a huffman tree
1809 of code lengths "cl". The code lengths used to describe this third tree are
1810 the code length code lengths ("clcl").
1811 */
1812
1813 /*The lz77 encoded data, represented with integers since there will also be length and distance codes in it*/
1814 uivector lz77_encoded;
1815 HuffmanTree tree_ll; /*tree for lit,len values*/
1816 HuffmanTree tree_d; /*tree for distance codes*/
1817 HuffmanTree tree_cl; /*tree for encoding the code lengths representing tree_ll and tree_d*/
1818 unsigned* frequencies_ll = 0; /*frequency of lit,len codes*/
1819 unsigned* frequencies_d = 0; /*frequency of dist codes*/
1820 unsigned* frequencies_cl = 0; /*frequency of code length codes*/
1821 unsigned* bitlen_lld = 0; /*lit,len,dist code lengths (int bits), literally (without repeat codes).*/
1822 unsigned* bitlen_lld_e = 0; /*bitlen_lld encoded with repeat codes (this is a rudimentary run length compression)*/
1823 size_t datasize = dataend - datapos;
1824
1825 /*
1826 If we could call "bitlen_cl" the the code length code lengths ("clcl"), that is the bit lengths of codes to represent
1827 tree_cl in CLCL_ORDER, then due to the huffman compression of huffman tree representations ("two levels"), there are
1828 some analogies:
1829 bitlen_lld is to tree_cl what data is to tree_ll and tree_d.
1830 bitlen_lld_e is to bitlen_lld what lz77_encoded is to data.
1831 bitlen_cl is to bitlen_lld_e what bitlen_lld is to lz77_encoded.
1832 */
1833
1834 unsigned BFINAL = final;
1835 size_t i;
1836 size_t numcodes_ll, numcodes_d, numcodes_lld, numcodes_lld_e, numcodes_cl;
1837 unsigned HLIT, HDIST, HCLEN;
1838
1839 uivector_init(&lz77_encoded);
1840 HuffmanTree_init(&tree_ll);
1841 HuffmanTree_init(&tree_d);
1842 HuffmanTree_init(&tree_cl);
1843 /* could fit on stack, but >1KB is on the larger side so allocate instead */
1844 frequencies_ll = (unsigned*)lodepng_malloc(286 * sizeof(*frequencies_ll));
1845 frequencies_d = (unsigned*)lodepng_malloc(30 * sizeof(*frequencies_d));
1846 frequencies_cl = (unsigned*)lodepng_malloc(NUM_CODE_LENGTH_CODES * sizeof(*frequencies_cl));
1847
1848 if(!frequencies_ll || !frequencies_d || !frequencies_cl) error = 83; /*alloc fail*/
1849
1850 /*This while loop never loops due to a break at the end, it is here to
1851 allow breaking out of it to the cleanup phase on error conditions.*/
1852 while(!error) {
1853 lodepng_memset(frequencies_ll, 0, 286 * sizeof(*frequencies_ll));
1854 lodepng_memset(frequencies_d, 0, 30 * sizeof(*frequencies_d));
1855 lodepng_memset(frequencies_cl, 0, NUM_CODE_LENGTH_CODES * sizeof(*frequencies_cl));
1856
1857 if(settings->use_lz77) {
1858 error = encodeLZ77(&lz77_encoded, hash, data, datapos, dataend, settings->windowsize,
1859 settings->minmatch, settings->nicematch, settings->lazymatching);
1860 if(error) break;
1861 } else {
1862 if(!uivector_resize(&lz77_encoded, datasize)) ERROR_BREAK(83 /*alloc fail*/);
1863 for(i = datapos; i < dataend; ++i) lz77_encoded.data[i - datapos] = data[i]; /*no LZ77, but still will be Huffman compressed*/
1864 }
1865
1866 /*Count the frequencies of lit, len and dist codes*/
1867 for(i = 0; i != lz77_encoded.size; ++i) {
1868 unsigned symbol = lz77_encoded.data[i];
1869 ++frequencies_ll[symbol];
1870 if(symbol > 256) {
1871 unsigned dist = lz77_encoded.data[i + 2];
1872 ++frequencies_d[dist];
1873 i += 3;
1874 }
1875 }
1876 frequencies_ll[256] = 1; /*there will be exactly 1 end code, at the end of the block*/
1877
1878 /*Make both huffman trees, one for the lit and len codes, one for the dist codes*/
1879 error = HuffmanTree_makeFromFrequencies(&tree_ll, frequencies_ll, 257, 286, 15);
1880 if(error) break;
1881 /*2, not 1, is chosen for mincodes: some buggy PNG decoders require at least 2 symbols in the dist tree*/
1882 error = HuffmanTree_makeFromFrequencies(&tree_d, frequencies_d, 2, 30, 15);
1883 if(error) break;
1884
1885 numcodes_ll = LODEPNG_MIN(tree_ll.numcodes, 286);
1886 numcodes_d = LODEPNG_MIN(tree_d.numcodes, 30);
1887 /*store the code lengths of both generated trees in bitlen_lld*/
1888 numcodes_lld = numcodes_ll + numcodes_d;
1889 bitlen_lld = (unsigned*)lodepng_malloc(numcodes_lld * sizeof(*bitlen_lld));
1890 /*numcodes_lld_e never needs more size than bitlen_lld*/
1891 bitlen_lld_e = (unsigned*)lodepng_malloc(numcodes_lld * sizeof(*bitlen_lld_e));
1892 if(!bitlen_lld || !bitlen_lld_e) ERROR_BREAK(83); /*alloc fail*/
1893 numcodes_lld_e = 0;
1894
1895 for(i = 0; i != numcodes_ll; ++i) bitlen_lld[i] = tree_ll.lengths[i];
1896 for(i = 0; i != numcodes_d; ++i) bitlen_lld[numcodes_ll + i] = tree_d.lengths[i];
1897
1898 /*run-length compress bitlen_ldd into bitlen_lld_e by using repeat codes 16 (copy length 3-6 times),
1899 17 (3-10 zeroes), 18 (11-138 zeroes)*/
1900 for(i = 0; i != numcodes_lld; ++i) {
1901 unsigned j = 0; /*amount of repetitions*/
1902 while(i + j + 1 < numcodes_lld && bitlen_lld[i + j + 1] == bitlen_lld[i]) ++j;
1903
1904 if(bitlen_lld[i] == 0 && j >= 2) /*repeat code for zeroes*/ {
1905 ++j; /*include the first zero*/
1906 if(j <= 10) /*repeat code 17 supports max 10 zeroes*/ {
1907 bitlen_lld_e[numcodes_lld_e++] = 17;
1908 bitlen_lld_e[numcodes_lld_e++] = j - 3;
1909 } else /*repeat code 18 supports max 138 zeroes*/ {
1910 if(j > 138) j = 138;
1911 bitlen_lld_e[numcodes_lld_e++] = 18;
1912 bitlen_lld_e[numcodes_lld_e++] = j - 11;
1913 }
1914 i += (j - 1);
1915 } else if(j >= 3) /*repeat code for value other than zero*/ {
1916 size_t k;
1917 unsigned num = j / 6u, rest = j % 6u;
1918 bitlen_lld_e[numcodes_lld_e++] = bitlen_lld[i];
1919 for(k = 0; k < num; ++k) {
1920 bitlen_lld_e[numcodes_lld_e++] = 16;
1921 bitlen_lld_e[numcodes_lld_e++] = 6 - 3;
1922 }
1923 if(rest >= 3) {
1924 bitlen_lld_e[numcodes_lld_e++] = 16;
1925 bitlen_lld_e[numcodes_lld_e++] = rest - 3;
1926 }
1927 else j -= rest;
1928 i += j;
1929 } else /*too short to benefit from repeat code*/ {
1930 bitlen_lld_e[numcodes_lld_e++] = bitlen_lld[i];
1931 }
1932 }
1933
1934 /*generate tree_cl, the huffmantree of huffmantrees*/
1935 for(i = 0; i != numcodes_lld_e; ++i) {
1936 ++frequencies_cl[bitlen_lld_e[i]];
1937 /*after a repeat code come the bits that specify the number of repetitions,
1938 those don't need to be in the frequencies_cl calculation*/
1939 if(bitlen_lld_e[i] >= 16) ++i;
1940 }
1941
1942 error = HuffmanTree_makeFromFrequencies(&tree_cl, frequencies_cl,
1943 NUM_CODE_LENGTH_CODES, NUM_CODE_LENGTH_CODES, 7);
1944 if(error) break;
1945
1946 /*compute amount of code-length-code-lengths to output*/
1947 numcodes_cl = NUM_CODE_LENGTH_CODES;
1948 /*trim zeros at the end (using CLCL_ORDER), but minimum size must be 4 (see HCLEN below)*/
1949 while(numcodes_cl > 4u && tree_cl.lengths[CLCL_ORDER[numcodes_cl - 1u]] == 0) {
1950 numcodes_cl--;
1951 }
1952
1953 /*
1954 Write everything into the output
1955
1956 After the BFINAL and BTYPE, the dynamic block consists out of the following:
1957 - 5 bits HLIT, 5 bits HDIST, 4 bits HCLEN
1958 - (HCLEN+4)*3 bits code lengths of code length alphabet
1959 - HLIT + 257 code lengths of lit/length alphabet (encoded using the code length
1960 alphabet, + possible repetition codes 16, 17, 18)
1961 - HDIST + 1 code lengths of distance alphabet (encoded using the code length
1962 alphabet, + possible repetition codes 16, 17, 18)
1963 - compressed data
1964 - 256 (end code)
1965 */
1966
1967 /*Write block type*/
1968 writeBits(writer, BFINAL, 1);
1969 writeBits(writer, 0, 1); /*first bit of BTYPE "dynamic"*/
1970 writeBits(writer, 1, 1); /*second bit of BTYPE "dynamic"*/
1971
1972 /*write the HLIT, HDIST and HCLEN values*/
1973 /*all three sizes take trimmed ending zeroes into account, done either by HuffmanTree_makeFromFrequencies
1974 or in the loop for numcodes_cl above, which saves space. */
1975 HLIT = (unsigned)(numcodes_ll - 257);
1976 HDIST = (unsigned)(numcodes_d - 1);
1977 HCLEN = (unsigned)(numcodes_cl - 4);
1978 writeBits(writer, HLIT, 5);
1979 writeBits(writer, HDIST, 5);
1980 writeBits(writer, HCLEN, 4);
1981
1982 /*write the code lengths of the code length alphabet ("bitlen_cl")*/
1983 for(i = 0; i != numcodes_cl; ++i) writeBits(writer, tree_cl.lengths[CLCL_ORDER[i]], 3);
1984
1985 /*write the lengths of the lit/len AND the dist alphabet*/
1986 for(i = 0; i != numcodes_lld_e; ++i) {
1987 writeBitsReversed(writer, tree_cl.codes[bitlen_lld_e[i]], tree_cl.lengths[bitlen_lld_e[i]]);
1988 /*extra bits of repeat codes*/
1989 if(bitlen_lld_e[i] == 16) writeBits(writer, bitlen_lld_e[++i], 2);
1990 else if(bitlen_lld_e[i] == 17) writeBits(writer, bitlen_lld_e[++i], 3);
1991 else if(bitlen_lld_e[i] == 18) writeBits(writer, bitlen_lld_e[++i], 7);
1992 }
1993
1994 /*write the compressed data symbols*/
1995 writeLZ77data(writer, &lz77_encoded, &tree_ll, &tree_d);
1996 /*error: the length of the end code 256 must be larger than 0*/
1997 if(tree_ll.lengths[256] == 0) ERROR_BREAK(64);
1998
1999 /*write the end code*/
2000 writeBitsReversed(writer, tree_ll.codes[256], tree_ll.lengths[256]);
2001
2002 break; /*end of error-while*/
2003 }
2004
2005 /*cleanup*/
2006 uivector_cleanup(&lz77_encoded);
2007 HuffmanTree_cleanup(&tree_ll);
2008 HuffmanTree_cleanup(&tree_d);
2009 HuffmanTree_cleanup(&tree_cl);
2010 lodepng_free(frequencies_ll);
2011 lodepng_free(frequencies_d);
2012 lodepng_free(frequencies_cl);
2013 lodepng_free(bitlen_lld);
2014 lodepng_free(bitlen_lld_e);
2015
2016 return error;
2017}

1604
1605 if(windowsize == 0 || windowsize > 32768) return 60; /*error: windowsize smaller/larger than allowed*/
1606 if((windowsize & (windowsize - 1)) != 0) return 90; /*error: must be power of two*/
1607
1608 if(nicematch > MAX_SUPPORTED_DEFLATE_LENGTH) nicematch = MAX_SUPPORTED_DEFLATE_LENGTH;
1609
1610 for(pos = inpos; pos < insize; ++pos) {
1611 size_t wpos = pos & (windowsize - 1); /*position for in 'circular' hash buffers*/
1612 unsigned chainlength = 0;
1613
1614 hashval = getHash(in, insize, pos);
1615
1616 if(usezeros && hashval == 0) {
1617 if(numzeros == 0) numzeros = countZeros(in, insize, pos);
1618 else if(pos + numzeros > insize || in[pos + numzeros - 1] != 0) --numzeros;
1619 } else {
1620 numzeros = 0;
1621 }
1622
1623 updateHashChain(hash, wpos, hashval, numzeros);
1624
1625 /*the length and offset found for the current position*/
1626 length = 0;
1627 offset = 0;
1628
1629 hashpos = hash->chain[wpos];
1630
1631 lastptr = &in[insize < pos + MAX_SUPPORTED_DEFLATE_LENGTH ? insize : pos + MAX_SUPPORTED_DEFLATE_LENGTH];
1632
1633 /*search for the longest string*/
1634 prev_offset = 0;
1635 for(;;) {
1636 if(chainlength++ >= maxchainlength) break;
1637 current_offset = (unsigned)(hashpos <= wpos ? wpos - hashpos : wpos - hashpos + windowsize);
1638
1639 if(current_offset < prev_offset) break; /*stop when went completely around the circular buffer*/
1640 prev_offset = current_offset;
1641 if(current_offset > 0) {
1642 /*test the next characters*/
1643 foreptr = &in[pos];
1644 backptr = &in[pos - current_offset];
1645
1646 /*common case in PNGs is lots of zeros. Quickly skip over them as a speedup*/
1647 if(numzeros >= 3) {
1648 unsigned skip = hash->zeros[hashpos];
1649 if(skip > numzeros) skip = numzeros;
1650 backptr += skip;
1651 foreptr += skip;
1652 }
1653
1654 while(foreptr != lastptr && *backptr == *foreptr) /*maximum supported length by deflate is max length*/ {
1655 ++backptr;
1656 ++foreptr;
1657 }
1658 current_length = (unsigned)(foreptr - &in[pos]);
1659
1660 if(current_length > length) {
1661 length = current_length; /*the longest length*/
1662 offset = current_offset; /*the offset that is related to this longest length*/
1663 /*jump out once a length of max length is found (speed gain). This also jumps
1664 out if length is MAX_SUPPORTED_DEFLATE_LENGTH*/
1665 if(current_length >= nicematch) break;
1666 }
1667 }
1668
1669 if(hashpos == hash->chain[hashpos]) break;
1670
1671 if(numzeros >= 3 && length > numzeros) {
1672 hashpos = hash->chainz[hashpos];
1673 if(hash->zeros[hashpos] != numzeros) break;
1674 } else {
1675 hashpos = hash->chain[hashpos];
1676 /*outdated hash value, happens if particular value was not encountered in whole last window*/
1677 if(hash->val[hashpos] != (int)hashval) break;
1678 }
1679 }
1680
1681 if(lazymatching) {
1682 if(!lazy && length >= 3 && length <= maxlazymatch && length < MAX_SUPPORTED_DEFLATE_LENGTH) {
1683 lazy = 1;
1684 lazylength = length;
1685 lazyoffset = offset;
1686 continue; /*try the next byte*/
1687 }
1688 if(lazy) {
1689 lazy = 0;
1690 if(pos == 0) ERROR_BREAK(81);
1691 if(length > lazylength + 1) {
1692 /*push the previous character as literal*/
1693 if(!uivector_push_back(out, in[pos - 1])) ERROR_BREAK(83 /*alloc fail*/);
1694 } else {
1695 length = lazylength;
1696 offset = lazyoffset;
1697 hash->head[hashval] = -1; /*the same hashchain update will be done, this ensures no wrong alteration*/
1698 hash->headz[numzeros] = -1; /*idem*/
1699 --pos;
1700 }
1701 }
1702 }
1703 if(length >= 3 && offset > windowsize) ERROR_BREAK(86 /*too big (or overflown negative) offset*/);
1704
1705 /*encode it as length/distance pair or literal value*/
1706 if(length < 3) /*only lengths of 3 or higher are supported as length/distance pair*/ {
1707 if(!uivector_push_back(out, in[pos])) ERROR_BREAK(83 /*alloc fail*/);
1708 } else if(length < minmatch || (length == 3 && offset > 4096)) {
1709 /*compensate for the fact that longer offsets have more extra bits, a
1710 length of only 3 may be not worth it then*/
1711 if(!uivector_push_back(out, in[pos])) ERROR_BREAK(83 /*alloc fail*/);
1712 } else {
1713 addLengthDistance(out, length, offset);
1714 for(i = 1; i < length; ++i) {
1715 ++pos;
1716 wpos = pos & (windowsize - 1);
1717 hashval = getHash(in, insize, pos);
1718 if(usezeros && hashval == 0) {
1719 if(numzeros == 0) numzeros = countZeros(in, insize, pos);
1720 else if(pos + numzeros > insize || in[pos + numzeros - 1] != 0) --numzeros;
1721 } else {
1722 numzeros = 0;
1723 }
1724 updateHashChain(hash, wpos, hashval, numzeros);
1725 }
1726 }
1727 } /*end of the loop through each character of input*/
1728
1729 return error;
1730}

5420 There is a heuristic called the minimum sum of absolute differences heuristic, suggested by the PNG standard:
5421 * If the image type is Palette, or the bit depth is smaller than 8, then do not filter the image (i.e.
5422 use fixed filtering, with the filter None).
5423 * (The other case) If the image type is Grayscale or RGB (with or without Alpha), and the bit depth is
5424 not smaller than 8, then use adaptive filtering heuristic as follows: independently for each row, apply
5425 all five filters and select the filter that produces the smallest sum of absolute values per row.

5355 for(i = 0; i != bytewidth; ++i) out[i] = scanline[i] - (prevline[i] >> 1);
5356 for(i = bytewidth; i < length; ++i) out[i] = scanline[i] - ((scanline[i - bytewidth] + prevline[i]) >> 1);
5357 } else {
5358 for(i = 0; i != bytewidth; ++i) out[i] = scanline[i];
5359 for(i = bytewidth; i < length; ++i) out[i] = scanline[i] - (scanline[i - bytewidth] >> 1);
5360 }
5361 break;
5362 case 4: /*Paeth*/
5363 if(prevline) {
5364 /*paethPredictor(0, prevline[i], 0) is always prevline[i]*/
5365 for(i = 0; i != bytewidth; ++i) out[i] = (scanline[i] - prevline[i]);
5366 for(i = bytewidth; i < length; ++i) {
5367 out[i] = (scanline[i] - paethPredictor(scanline[i - bytewidth], prevline[i], prevline[i - bytewidth]));
5368 }
5369 } else {
5370 for(i = 0; i != bytewidth; ++i) out[i] = scanline[i];
5371 /*paethPredictor(scanline[i - bytewidth], 0, 0) is always scanline[i - bytewidth]*/
5372 for(i = bytewidth; i < length; ++i) out[i] = (scanline[i] - scanline[i - bytewidth]);
5373 }
5374 break;
5375 default: return; /*invalid filter type given*/
5376 }
5377}

1535 unsigned result = 0;
1536 if(pos + 2 < size) {
1537 /*A simple shift and xor hash is used. Since the data of PNGs is dominated
1538 by zeroes due to the filters, a better hash does not have a significant
1539 effect on speed in traversing the chain, and causes more time spend on
1540 calculating the hash.*/

1181 while(i < HLIT + HDIST) {
1182 unsigned code;
1183 ensureBits25(reader, 22); /* up to 15 bits for huffman code, up to 7 extra bits below*/
1184 code = huffmanDecodeSymbol(reader, &tree_cl);
1185 if(code <= 15) /*a length code*/ {
1186 if(i < HLIT) bitlen_ll[i] = code;
1187 else bitlen_d[i - HLIT] = code;
1188 ++i;
1189 } else if(code == 16) /*repeat previous*/ {
1190 unsigned replength = 3; /*read in the 2 bits that indicate repeat length (3-6)*/
1191 unsigned value; /*set value to the previous code*/
1192
1193 if(i == 0) ERROR_BREAK(54); /*can't repeat previous if i is 0*/
1194
1195 replength += readBits(reader, 2);
1196
1197 if(i < HLIT + 1) value = bitlen_ll[i - 1];
1198 else value = bitlen_d[i - HLIT - 1];
1199 /*repeat this value in the next lengths*/
1200 for(n = 0; n < replength; ++n) {
1201 if(i >= HLIT + HDIST) ERROR_BREAK(13); /*error: i is larger than the amount of codes*/
1202 if(i < HLIT) bitlen_ll[i] = value;
1203 else bitlen_d[i - HLIT] = value;
1204 ++i;
1205 }
1206 } else if(code == 17) /*repeat "0" 3-10 times*/ {
1207 unsigned replength = 3; /*read in the bits that indicate repeat length*/
1208 replength += readBits(reader, 3);
1209
1210 /*repeat this value in the next lengths*/
1211 for(n = 0; n < replength; ++n) {
1212 if(i >= HLIT + HDIST) ERROR_BREAK(14); /*error: i is larger than the amount of codes*/
1213
1214 if(i < HLIT) bitlen_ll[i] = 0;
1215 else bitlen_d[i - HLIT] = 0;
1216 ++i;
1217 }
1218 } else if(code == 18) /*repeat "0" 11-138 times*/ {
1219 unsigned replength = 11; /*read in the bits that indicate repeat length*/
1220 replength += readBits(reader, 7);
1221
1222 /*repeat this value in the next lengths*/
1223 for(n = 0; n < replength; ++n) {
1224 if(i >= HLIT + HDIST) ERROR_BREAK(15); /*error: i is larger than the amount of codes*/
1225
1226 if(i < HLIT) bitlen_ll[i] = 0;
1227 else bitlen_d[i - HLIT] = 0;
1228 ++i;
1229 }
1230 } else /*if(code == INVALIDSYMBOL)*/ {
1231 ERROR_BREAK(16); /*error: tried to read disallowed huffman symbol*/
1232 }
1233 /*check if any of the ensureBits above went out of bounds*/
1234 if(reader->bp > reader->bitsize) {
1235 /*return error code 10 or 11 depending on the situation that happened in huffmanDecodeSymbol
1236 (10=no endcode, 11=wrong jump outside of tree)*/
1237 /* TODO: revise error codes 10,11,50: the above comment is no longer valid */
1238 ERROR_BREAK(50); /*error, bit pointer jumps past memory*/
1239 }
1240 }
1241 if(error) break;
1242
1243 if(bitlen_ll[256] == 0) ERROR_BREAK(64); /*the length of the end code 256 must be larger than 0*/
1244
1245 /*now we've finally got HLIT and HDIST, so generate the code trees, and the function is done*/
1246 error = HuffmanTree_makeFromLengths(tree_ll, bitlen_ll, NUM_DEFLATE_CODE_SYMBOLS, 15);
1247 if(error) break;
1248 error = HuffmanTree_makeFromLengths(tree_d, bitlen_d, NUM_DISTANCE_SYMBOLS, 15);
1249
1250 break; /*end of error-while*/
1251 }
1252
1253 lodepng_free(bitlen_cl);
1254 lodepng_free(bitlen_ll);
1255 lodepng_free(bitlen_d);
1256 HuffmanTree_cleanup(&tree_cl);
1257
1258 return error;
1259}

◆ HuffmanTree_makeTable()

static unsigned HuffmanTree_makeTable ( HuffmanTree *  tree)
static
689 {
690 static const unsigned headsize = 1u << FIRSTBITS; /*size of the first table*/
691 static const unsigned mask = (1u << FIRSTBITS) /*headsize*/ - 1u;
692 size_t i, numpresent, pointer, size; /*total table size*/
693 unsigned* maxlens = (unsigned*)lodepng_malloc(headsize * sizeof(unsigned));
694 if(!maxlens) return 83; /*alloc fail*/
695
696 /* compute maxlens: max total bit length of symbols sharing prefix in the first table*/
697 lodepng_memset(maxlens, 0, headsize * sizeof(*maxlens));
698 for(i = 0; i < tree->numcodes; i++) {
699 unsigned symbol = tree->codes[i];
700 unsigned l = tree->lengths[i];
701 unsigned index;
702 if(l <= FIRSTBITS) continue; /*symbols that fit in first table don't increase secondary table size*/
703 /*get the FIRSTBITS MSBs, the MSBs of the symbol are encoded first. See later comment about the reversing*/
704 index = reverseBits(symbol >> (l - FIRSTBITS), FIRSTBITS);
705 maxlens[index] = LODEPNG_MAX(maxlens[index], l);
706 }
707 /* compute total table size: size of first table plus all secondary tables for symbols longer than FIRSTBITS */
708 size = headsize;
709 for(i = 0; i < headsize; ++i) {
710 unsigned l = maxlens[i];
711 if(l > FIRSTBITS) size += (1u << (l - FIRSTBITS));
712 }
713 tree->table_len = (unsigned char*)lodepng_malloc(size * sizeof(*tree->table_len));
714 tree->table_value = (unsigned short*)lodepng_malloc(size * sizeof(*tree->table_value));
715 if(!tree->table_len || !tree->table_value) {
716 lodepng_free(maxlens);
717 /* freeing tree->table values is done at a higher scope */
718 return 83; /*alloc fail*/
719 }
720 /*initialize with an invalid length to indicate unused entries*/
721 for(i = 0; i < size; ++i) tree->table_len[i] = 16;
722
723 /*fill in the first table for long symbols: max prefix size and pointer to secondary tables*/
724 pointer = headsize;
725 for(i = 0; i < headsize; ++i) {
726 unsigned l = maxlens[i];
727 if(l <= FIRSTBITS) continue;
728 tree->table_len[i] = l;
729 tree->table_value[i] = pointer;
730 pointer += (1u << (l - FIRSTBITS));
731 }
732 lodepng_free(maxlens);
733
734 /*fill in the first table for short symbols, or secondary table for long symbols*/
735 numpresent = 0;
736 for(i = 0; i < tree->numcodes; ++i) {
737 unsigned l = tree->lengths[i];
738 unsigned symbol = tree->codes[i]; /*the huffman bit pattern. i itself is the value.*/
739 /*reverse bits, because the huffman bits are given in MSB first order but the bit reader reads LSB first*/
740 unsigned reverse = reverseBits(symbol, l);
741 if(l == 0) continue;
742 numpresent++;
743
744 if(l <= FIRSTBITS) {
745 /*short symbol, fully in first table, replicated num times if l < FIRSTBITS*/
746 unsigned num = 1u << (FIRSTBITS - l);
747 unsigned j;
748 for(j = 0; j < num; ++j) {
749 /*bit reader will read the l bits of symbol first, the remaining FIRSTBITS - l bits go to the MSB's*/
750 unsigned index = reverse | (j << l);
751 if(tree->table_len[index] != 16) return 55; /*invalid tree: long symbol shares prefix with short symbol*/
752 tree->table_len[index] = l;
753 tree->table_value[index] = i;
754 }
755 } else {
756 /*long symbol, shares prefix with other long symbols in first lookup table, needs second lookup*/
757 /*the FIRSTBITS MSBs of the symbol are the first table index*/
758 unsigned index = reverse & mask;
759 unsigned maxlen = tree->table_len[index];
760 /*log2 of secondary table length, should be >= l - FIRSTBITS*/
761 unsigned tablelen = maxlen - FIRSTBITS;
762 unsigned start = tree->table_value[index]; /*starting index in secondary table*/
763 unsigned num = 1u << (tablelen - (l - FIRSTBITS)); /*amount of entries of this symbol in secondary table*/
764 unsigned j;
765 if(maxlen < l) return 55; /*invalid tree: long symbol shares prefix with short symbol*/
766 for(j = 0; j < num; ++j) {
767 unsigned reverse2 = reverse >> FIRSTBITS; /* l - FIRSTBITS bits */
768 unsigned index2 = start + (reverse2 | (j << (l - FIRSTBITS)));
769 tree->table_len[index2] = l;
770 tree->table_value[index2] = i;
771 }
772 }
773 }
774
775 if(numpresent < 2) {
776 /* In case of exactly 1 symbol, in theory the huffman symbol needs 0 bits,
777 but deflate uses 1 bit instead. In case of 0 symbols, no symbols can
778 appear at all, but such huffman tree could still exist (e.g. if distance
779 codes are never used). In both cases, not all symbols of the table will be
780 filled in. Fill them in with an invalid symbol value so returning them from
781 huffmanDecodeSymbol will cause error. */
782 for(i = 0; i < size; ++i) {
783 if(tree->table_len[i] == 16) {
784 /* As length, use a value smaller than FIRSTBITS for the head table,
785 and a value larger than FIRSTBITS for the secondary table, to ensure
786 valid behavior for advanceBits when reading this symbol. */
787 tree->table_len[i] = (i < headsize) ? 1 : (FIRSTBITS + 1);
788 tree->table_value[i] = INVALIDSYMBOL;
789 }
790 }
791 } else {
792 /* A good huffman tree has N * 2 - 1 nodes, of which N - 1 are internal nodes.
793 If that is not the case (due to too long length codes), the table will not
794 have been fully used, and this is an error (not all bit combinations can be
795 decoded): an oversubscribed huffman tree, indicated by error 55. */
796 for(i = 0; i < size; ++i) {
797 if(tree->table_len[i] == 16) return 55;
798 }
799 }
800
801 return 0;
802}

1311 if(numextrabits_d != 0) {
1312 /* bits already ensured above */
1313 distance += readBits(reader, numextrabits_d);
1314 }
1315
1316 /*part 5: fill in all the out[n] values based on the length and dist*/
1317 start = out->size;
1318 if(distance > start) ERROR_BREAK(52); /*too long backward distance*/
1319 backward = start - distance;
1320
1321 if(!ucvector_resize(out, out->size + length)) ERROR_BREAK(83 /*alloc fail*/);
1322 if(distance < length) {
1323 size_t forward;
1324 lodepng_memcpy(out->data + start, out->data + backward, distance);
1325 start += distance;
1326 for(forward = distance; forward < length; ++forward) {
1327 out->data[start++] = out->data[backward++];
1328 }
1329 } else {
1330 lodepng_memcpy(out->data + start, out->data + backward, length);
1331 }
1332 } else if(code_ll == 256) {
1333 break; /*end code, break the loop*/
1334 } else /*if(code_ll == INVALIDSYMBOL)*/ {
1335 ERROR_BREAK(16); /*error: tried to read disallowed huffman symbol*/
1336 }
1337 /*check if any of the ensureBits above went out of bounds*/
1338 if(reader->bp > reader->bitsize) {
1339 /*return error code 10 or 11 depending on the situation that happened in huffmanDecodeSymbol
1340 (10=no endcode, 11=wrong jump outside of tree)*/
1341 /* TODO: revise error codes 10,11,50: the above comment is no longer valid */
1342 ERROR_BREAK(51); /*error, bit pointer jumps past memory*/
1343 }
1344 }
1345
1346 HuffmanTree_cleanup(&tree_ll);
1347 HuffmanTree_cleanup(&tree_d);
1348
1349 return error;
1350}

◆ isGrayICCProfile()

static unsigned isGrayICCProfile ( const unsigned char *  profile,
unsigned  size 
)
static
5749 {
5750 /*
5751 It is a gray profile if bytes 16-19 are "GRAY", rgb profile if bytes 16-19
5752 are "RGB ". We do not perform any full parsing of the ICC profile here, other
5753 than check those 4 bytes to grayscale profile. Other than that, validity of
5754 the profile is not checked. This is needed only because the PNG specification
5755 requires using a non-gray color model if there is an ICC profile with "RGB "
5756 (sadly limiting compression opportunities if the input data is grayscale RGB
5757 data), and requires using a gray color model if it is "GRAY".
5758 */
5759 if(size < 20) return 0;
5760 return profile[16] == 'G' && profile[17] == 'R' && profile[18] == 'A' && profile[19] == 'Y';
5761}

2656 {

3688
3689 stats->numpixels += numpixels;
3690
3691 /*if palette not allowed, no need to compute numcolors*/
3692 if(!stats->allow_palette) numcolors_done = 1;
3693
3694 color_tree_init(&tree);
3695
3696 /*If the stats was already filled in from previous data, fill its palette in tree
3697 and mark things as done already if we know they are the most expensive case already*/
3698 if(stats->alpha) alpha_done = 1;
3699 if(stats->colored) colored_done = 1;
3700 if(stats->bits == 16) numcolors_done = 1;
3701 if(stats->bits >= bpp) bits_done = 1;
3702 if(stats->numcolors >= maxnumcolors) numcolors_done = 1;

3708 if(error) goto cleanup;
3709 }
3710 }

3717 if((r & 255) != ((r >> 8) & 255) || (g & 255) != ((g >> 8) & 255) ||
3718 (b & 255) != ((b >> 8) & 255) || (a & 255) != ((a >> 8) & 255)) /*first and second byte differ*/ {
3719 stats->bits = 16;
3720 sixteen = 1;
3721 bits_done = 1;
3722 numcolors_done = 1; /*counting colors no longer useful, palette doesn't support 16-bit*/

3724 }
3725 }
3726 }

3733

3735 stats->colored = 1;
3736 colored_done = 1;
3737 }

3742 stats->alpha = 1;
3743 stats->key = 0;
3744 alpha_done = 1;
3745 } else if(a == 0 && !stats->alpha && !stats->key) {

3766 stats->key = 0;
3767 alpha_done = 1;

3779 if(bits > stats->bits) stats->bits = bits;

3791 if(a != 255 && (a != 0 || (stats->key && !matchkey))) {
3792 stats->alpha = 1;
3793 stats->key = 0;
3794 alpha_done = 1;
3795 if(stats->bits < 8) stats->bits = 8; /*PNG has no alphachannel modes with less than 8-bit per channel*/
3796 } else if(a == 0 && !stats->alpha && !stats->key) {

3803 stats->alpha = 1;

3805 alpha_done = 1;
3806 if(stats->bits < 8) stats->bits = 8; /*PNG has no alphachannel modes with less than 8-bit per channel*/
3807 }
3808 }
3809

3813 if(error) goto cleanup;
3814 if(stats->numcolors < 256) {
3815 unsigned char* p = stats->palette;
3816 unsigned n = stats->numcolors;
3817 p[n * 4 + 0] = r;
3818 p[n * 4 + 1] = g;
3819 p[n * 4 + 2] = b;
3820 p[n * 4 + 3] = a;
3821 }
3822 ++stats->numcolors;
3823 numcolors_done = stats->numcolors >= maxnumcolors;
3824 }
3825 }

3827 if(alpha_done && numcolors_done && colored_done && bits_done) break;
3828 }

3835 stats->alpha = 1;
3836 stats->key = 0;
3837 alpha_done = 1;
3838 if(stats->bits < 8) stats->bits = 8; /*PNG has no alphachannel modes with less than 8-bit per channel*/
3839 }
3840 }
3841 }
3842
3843 /*make the stats's key always 16-bit for consistency - repeat each byte twice*/
3844 stats->key_r += (stats->key_r << 8);
3845 stats->key_g += (stats->key_g << 8);
3846 stats->key_b += (stats->key_b << 8);

3507 ColorTree tree;
3508 size_t numpixels = (size_t)w * (size_t)h;
3509 unsigned error = 0;
3510
3511 if(mode_in->colortype == LCT_PALETTE && !mode_in->palette) {
3512 return 107; /* error: must provide palette if input mode is palette */
3513 }
3514
3515 if(lodepng_color_mode_equal(mode_out, mode_in)) {
3516 size_t numbytes = lodepng_get_raw_size(w, h, mode_in);
3517 lodepng_memcpy(out, in, numbytes);
3518 return 0;
3519 }
3520
3521 if(mode_out->colortype == LCT_PALETTE) {
3522 size_t palettesize = mode_out->palettesize;
3523 const unsigned char* palette = mode_out->palette;
3524 size_t palsize = (size_t)1u << mode_out->bitdepth;
3525 /*if the user specified output palette but did not give the values, assume
3526 they want the values of the input color type (assuming that one is palette).
3527 Note that we never create a new palette ourselves.*/
3528 if(palettesize == 0) {
3529 palettesize = mode_in->palettesize;
3530 palette = mode_in->palette;
3531 /*if the input was also palette with same bitdepth, then the color types are also
3532 equal, so copy literally. This to preserve the exact indices that were in the PNG
3533 even in case there are duplicate colors in the palette.*/
3534 if(mode_in->colortype == LCT_PALETTE && mode_in->bitdepth == mode_out->bitdepth) {
3535 size_t numbytes = lodepng_get_raw_size(w, h, mode_in);
3536 lodepng_memcpy(out, in, numbytes);
3537 return 0;
3538 }
3539 }
3540 if(palettesize < palsize) palsize = palettesize;
3541 color_tree_init(&tree);
3542 for(i = 0; i != palsize; ++i) {
3543 const unsigned char* p = &palette[i * 4];
3544 error = color_tree_add(&tree, p[0], p[1], p[2], p[3], (unsigned)i);
3545 if(error) break;
3546 }
3547 }
3548
3549 if(!error) {
3550 if(mode_in->bitdepth == 16 && mode_out->bitdepth == 16) {
3551 for(i = 0; i != numpixels; ++i) {
3552 unsigned short r = 0, g = 0, b = 0, a = 0;
3553 getPixelColorRGBA16(&r, &g, &b, &a, in, i, mode_in);
3554 rgba16ToPixel(out, i, mode_out, r, g, b, a);
3555 }
3556 } else if(mode_out->bitdepth == 8 && mode_out->colortype == LCT_RGBA) {
3557 getPixelColorsRGBA8(out, numpixels, in, mode_in);
3558 } else if(mode_out->bitdepth == 8 && mode_out->colortype == LCT_RGB) {
3559 getPixelColorsRGB8(out, numpixels, in, mode_in);
3560 } else {
3561 unsigned char r = 0, g = 0, b = 0, a = 0;
3562 for(i = 0; i != numpixels; ++i) {
3563 getPixelColorRGBA8(&r, &g, &b, &a, in, i, mode_in);
3564 error = rgba8ToPixel(out, i, mode_out, &tree, r, g, b, a);
3565 if(error) break;
3566 }
3567 }
3568 }
3569
3570 if(mode_out->colortype == LCT_PALETTE) {
3571 color_tree_cleanup(&tree);
3572 }
3573
3574 return error;
3575}

5825#ifdef LODEPNG_COMPILE_ANCILLARY_CHUNKS
5826 if(info_png->background_defined) {
5827 /*the background chunk's color must be taken into account as well*/
5828 unsigned r = 0, g = 0, b = 0;
5829 LodePNGColorMode mode16 = lodepng_color_mode_make(LCT_RGB, 16);
5830 lodepng_convert_rgb(&r, &g, &b, info_png->background_r, info_png->background_g, info_png->background_b, &mode16, &info_png->color);
5831 state->error = lodepng_color_stats_add(&stats, r, g, b, 65535);
5832 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5833 }
5834#endif /* LODEPNG_COMPILE_ANCILLARY_CHUNKS */
5835 state->error = auto_choose_color(&info.color, &state->info_raw, &stats);
5836 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5837#ifdef LODEPNG_COMPILE_ANCILLARY_CHUNKS
5838 /*also convert the background chunk*/
5839 if(info_png->background_defined) {
5840 if(lodepng_convert_rgb(&info.background_r, &info.background_g, &info.background_b,
5841 info_png->background_r, info_png->background_g, info_png->background_b, &info.color, &info_png->color)) {
5842 state->error = 104;
5843 goto cleanup;
5844 }
5845 }
5846#endif /* LODEPNG_COMPILE_ANCILLARY_CHUNKS */
5847 }
5848#ifdef LODEPNG_COMPILE_ANCILLARY_CHUNKS
5849 if(info_png->iccp_defined) {
5850 unsigned gray_icc = isGrayICCProfile(info_png->iccp_profile, info_png->iccp_profile_size);
5851 unsigned rgb_icc = isRGBICCProfile(info_png->iccp_profile, info_png->iccp_profile_size);
5852 unsigned gray_png = info.color.colortype == LCT_GREY || info.color.colortype == LCT_GREY_ALPHA;
5853 if(!gray_icc && !rgb_icc) {
5854 state->error = 100; /* Disallowed profile color type for PNG */
5855 goto cleanup;
5856 }
5857 if(gray_icc != gray_png) {
5858 /*Not allowed to use RGB/RGBA/palette with GRAY ICC profile or vice versa,
5859 or in case of auto_convert, it wasn't possible to find appropriate model*/
5860 state->error = state->encoder.auto_convert ? 102 : 101;
5861 goto cleanup;
5862 }
5863 }
5864#endif /*LODEPNG_COMPILE_ANCILLARY_CHUNKS*/
5865 if(!lodepng_color_mode_equal(&state->info_raw, &info.color)) {
5866 unsigned char* converted;
5867 size_t size = ((size_t)w * (size_t)h * (size_t)lodepng_get_bpp(&info.color) + 7u) / 8u;
5868
5869 converted = (unsigned char*)lodepng_malloc(size);
5870 if(!converted && size) state->error = 83; /*alloc fail*/
5871 if(!state->error) {
5872 state->error = lodepng_convert(converted, image, &info.color, &state->info_raw, w, h);
5873 }
5874 if(!state->error) {
5875 state->error = preProcessScanlines(&data, &datasize, converted, w, h, &info, &state->encoder);
5876 }
5877 lodepng_free(converted);
5878 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5879 } else {
5880 state->error = preProcessScanlines(&data, &datasize, image, w, h, &info, &state->encoder);
5881 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5882 }
5883
5884 /* output all PNG chunks */ {
5885#ifdef LODEPNG_COMPILE_ANCILLARY_CHUNKS
5886 size_t i;
5887#endif /*LODEPNG_COMPILE_ANCILLARY_CHUNKS*/
5888 /*write signature and chunks*/
5889 state->error = writeSignature(&outv);
5890 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5891 /*IHDR*/
5892 state->error = addChunk_IHDR(&outv, w, h, info.color.colortype, info.color.bitdepth, info.interlace_method);
5893 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5894#ifdef LODEPNG_COMPILE_ANCILLARY_CHUNKS
5895 /*unknown chunks between IHDR and PLTE*/
5896 if(info.unknown_chunks_data[0]) {
5897 state->error = addUnknownChunks(&outv, info.unknown_chunks_data[0], info.unknown_chunks_size[0]);
5898 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5899 }
5900 /*color profile chunks must come before PLTE */
5901 if(info.iccp_defined) {
5902 state->error = addChunk_iCCP(&outv, &info, &state->encoder.zlibsettings);
5903 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5904 }
5905 if(info.srgb_defined) {
5906 state->error = addChunk_sRGB(&outv, &info);
5907 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5908 }
5909 if(info.gama_defined) {
5910 state->error = addChunk_gAMA(&outv, &info);
5911 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5912 }
5913 if(info.chrm_defined) {
5914 state->error = addChunk_cHRM(&outv, &info);
5915 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5916 }
5917#endif /*LODEPNG_COMPILE_ANCILLARY_CHUNKS*/
5918 /*PLTE*/
5919 if(info.color.colortype == LCT_PALETTE) {
5920 state->error = addChunk_PLTE(&outv, &info.color);
5921 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5922 }
5923 if(state->encoder.force_palette && (info.color.colortype == LCT_RGB || info.color.colortype == LCT_RGBA)) {
5924 /*force_palette means: write suggested palette for truecolor in PLTE chunk*/
5925 state->error = addChunk_PLTE(&outv, &info.color);
5926 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5927 }
5928 /*tRNS (this will only add if when necessary) */
5929 state->error = addChunk_tRNS(&outv, &info.color);
5930 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5931#ifdef LODEPNG_COMPILE_ANCILLARY_CHUNKS
5932 /*bKGD (must come between PLTE and the IDAt chunks*/
5933 if(info.background_defined) {
5934 state->error = addChunk_bKGD(&outv, &info);
5935 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5936 }
5937 /*pHYs (must come before the IDAT chunks)*/
5938 if(info.phys_defined) {
5939 state->error = addChunk_pHYs(&outv, &info);
5940 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5941 }
5942
5943 /*unknown chunks between PLTE and IDAT*/
5944 if(info.unknown_chunks_data[1]) {
5945 state->error = addUnknownChunks(&outv, info.unknown_chunks_data[1], info.unknown_chunks_size[1]);
5946 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5947 }
5948#endif /*LODEPNG_COMPILE_ANCILLARY_CHUNKS*/
5949 /*IDAT (multiple IDAT chunks must be consecutive)*/
5950 state->error = addChunk_IDAT(&outv, data, datasize, &state->encoder.zlibsettings);
5951 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5952#ifdef LODEPNG_COMPILE_ANCILLARY_CHUNKS
5953 /*tIME*/
5954 if(info.time_defined) {
5955 state->error = addChunk_tIME(&outv, &info.time);
5956 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5957 }
5958 /*tEXt and/or zTXt*/
5959 for(i = 0; i != info.text_num; ++i) {
5960 if(lodepng_strlen(info.text_keys[i]) > 79) {
5961 state->error = 66; /*text chunk too large*/
5962 goto cleanup;
5963 }
5964 if(lodepng_strlen(info.text_keys[i]) < 1) {
5965 state->error = 67; /*text chunk too small*/
5966 goto cleanup;
5967 }
5968 if(state->encoder.text_compression) {
5969 state->error = addChunk_zTXt(&outv, info.text_keys[i], info.text_strings[i], &state->encoder.zlibsettings);
5970 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5971 } else {
5972 state->error = addChunk_tEXt(&outv, info.text_keys[i], info.text_strings[i]);
5973 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5974 }
5975 }
5976 /*LodePNG version id in text chunk*/
5977 if(state->encoder.add_id) {
5978 unsigned already_added_id_text = 0;
5979 for(i = 0; i != info.text_num; ++i) {
5980 const char* k = info.text_keys[i];
5981 /* Could use strcmp, but we're not calling or reimplementing this C library function for this use only */
5982 if(k[0] == 'L' && k[1] == 'o' && k[2] == 'd' && k[3] == 'e' &&
5983 k[4] == 'P' && k[5] == 'N' && k[6] == 'G' && k[7] == '\0') {
5984 already_added_id_text = 1;
5985 break;
5986 }
5987 }
5988 if(already_added_id_text == 0) {
5989 state->error = addChunk_tEXt(&outv, "LodePNG", LODEPNG_VERSION_STRING); /*it's shorter as tEXt than as zTXt chunk*/
5990 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
5991 }
5992 }
5993 /*iTXt*/
5994 for(i = 0; i != info.itext_num; ++i) {
5995 if(lodepng_strlen(info.itext_keys[i]) > 79) {
5996 state->error = 66; /*text chunk too large*/
5997 goto cleanup;
5998 }
5999 if(lodepng_strlen(info.itext_keys[i]) < 1) {
6000 state->error = 67; /*text chunk too small*/
6001 goto cleanup;
6002 }
6003 state->error = addChunk_iTXt(
6004 &outv, state->encoder.text_compression,
6005 info.itext_keys[i], info.itext_langtags[i], info.itext_transkeys[i], info.itext_strings[i],
6006 &state->encoder.zlibsettings);
6007 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
6008 }
6009
6010 /*unknown chunks between IDAT and IEND*/
6011 if(info.unknown_chunks_data[2]) {
6012 state->error = addUnknownChunks(&outv, info.unknown_chunks_data[2], info.unknown_chunks_size[2]);
6013 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
6014 }
6015#endif /*LODEPNG_COMPILE_ANCILLARY_CHUNKS*/
6016 state->error = addChunk_IEND(&outv);
6017 if(state->error) goto cleanup;
6018 }
6019
6020cleanup:
6021 lodepng_info_cleanup(&info);
6022 lodepng_free(data);
6023
6024 /*instead of cleaning the vector up, give it to the output*/
6025 *out = outv.data;
6026 *outsize = outv.size;
6027
6028 return state->error;
6029}

968 unsigned error = 0;
969 unsigned i;
970 size_t numpresent = 0; /*number of symbols with non-zero frequency*/
971 BPMNode* leaves; /*the symbols, only those with > 0 frequency*/
972
973 if(numcodes == 0) return 80; /*error: a tree of 0 symbols is not supposed to be made*/
974 if((1u << maxbitlen) < (unsigned)numcodes) return 80; /*error: represent all symbols*/
975
976 leaves = (BPMNode*)lodepng_malloc(numcodes * sizeof(*leaves));
977 if(!leaves) return 83; /*alloc fail*/
978
979 for(i = 0; i != numcodes; ++i) {
980 if(frequencies[i] > 0) {
981 leaves[numpresent].weight = (int)frequencies[i];
982 leaves[numpresent].index = i;
983 ++numpresent;
984 }
985 }
986
987 lodepng_memset(lengths, 0, numcodes * sizeof(*lengths));
988
989 /*ensure at least two present symbols. There should be at least one symbol
990 according to RFC 1951 section 3.2.7. Some decoders incorrectly require two. To
991 make these work as well ensure there are at least two symbols. The
992 Package-Merge code below also doesn't work correctly if there's only one
993 symbol, it'd give it the theoretical 0 bits but in practice zlib wants 1 bit*/
994 if(numpresent == 0) {
995 lengths[0] = lengths[1] = 1; /*note that for RFC 1951 section 3.2.7, only lengths[0] = 1 is needed*/
996 } else if(numpresent == 1) {
997 lengths[leaves[0].index] = 1;
998 lengths[leaves[0].index == 0 ? 1 : 0] = 1;
999 } else {
1000 BPMLists lists;
1001 BPMNode* node;
1002
1003 bpmnode_sort(leaves, numpresent);
1004
1005 lists.listsize = maxbitlen;
1006 lists.memsize = 2 * maxbitlen * (maxbitlen + 1);
1007 lists.nextfree = 0;
1008 lists.numfree = lists.memsize;
1009 lists.memory = (BPMNode*)lodepng_malloc(lists.memsize * sizeof(*lists.memory));
1010 lists.freelist = (BPMNode**)lodepng_malloc(lists.memsize * sizeof(BPMNode*));
1011 lists.chains0 = (BPMNode**)lodepng_malloc(lists.listsize * sizeof(BPMNode*));
1012 lists.chains1 = (BPMNode**)lodepng_malloc(lists.listsize * sizeof(BPMNode*));
1013 if(!lists.memory || !lists.freelist || !lists.chains0 || !lists.chains1) error = 83; /*alloc fail*/
1014
1015 if(!error) {
1016 for(i = 0; i != lists.memsize; ++i) lists.freelist[i] = &lists.memory[i];
1017
1018 bpmnode_create(&lists, leaves[0].weight, 1, 0);
1019 bpmnode_create(&lists, leaves[1].weight, 2, 0);
1020
1021 for(i = 0; i != lists.listsize; ++i) {
1022 lists.chains0[i] = &lists.memory[0];
1023 lists.chains1[i] = &lists.memory[1];
1024 }
1025
1026 /*each boundaryPM call adds one chain to the last list, and we need 2 * numpresent - 2 chains.*/
1027 for(i = 2; i != 2 * numpresent - 2; ++i) boundaryPM(&lists, leaves, numpresent, (int)maxbitlen - 1, (int)i);
1028

1030 for(i = 0; i != node->index; ++i) ++lengths[leaves[i].index];
1031 }
1032 }
1033

1035 lodepng_free(lists.freelist);
1036 lodepng_free(lists.chains0);
1037 lodepng_free(lists.chains1);

4019 LodePNGInfo* info = &state->info_png;
4020 if(insize == 0 || in == 0) {
4021 CERROR_RETURN_ERROR(state->error, 48); /*error: the given data is empty*/
4022 }
4023 if(insize < 33) {
4024 CERROR_RETURN_ERROR(state->error, 27); /*error: the data length is smaller than the length of a PNG header*/
4025 }
4026
4027 /*when decoding a new PNG image, make sure all parameters created after previous decoding are reset*/
4028 /* TODO: remove this. One should use a new LodePNGState for new sessions */
4029 lodepng_info_cleanup(info);
4030 lodepng_info_init(info);
4031
4032 if(in[0] != 137 || in[1] != 80 || in[2] != 78 || in[3] != 71
4033 || in[4] != 13 || in[5] != 10 || in[6] != 26 || in[7] != 10) {
4034 CERROR_RETURN_ERROR(state->error, 28); /*error: the first 8 bytes are not the correct PNG signature*/
4035 }
4036 if(lodepng_chunk_length(in + 8) != 13) {
4037 CERROR_RETURN_ERROR(state->error, 94); /*error: header size must be 13 bytes*/
4038 }
4039 if(!lodepng_chunk_type_equals(in + 8, "IHDR")) {
4040 CERROR_RETURN_ERROR(state->error, 29); /*error: it doesn't start with a IHDR chunk!*/
4041 }
4042
4043 /*read the values given in the header*/
4044 width = lodepng_read32bitInt(&in[16]);
4045 height = lodepng_read32bitInt(&in[20]);
4046 /*TODO: remove the undocumented feature that allows to give null pointers to width or height*/
4047 if(w) *w = width;
4048 if(h) *h = height;
4049 info->color.bitdepth = in[24];
4050 info->color.colortype = (LodePNGColorType)in[25];
4051 info->compression_method = in[26];
4052 info->filter_method = in[27];
4053 info->interlace_method = in[28];
4054
4055 /*errors returned only after the parsing so other values are still output*/
4056
4057 /*error: invalid image size*/
4058 if(width == 0 || height == 0) CERROR_RETURN_ERROR(state->error, 93);
4059 /*error: invalid colortype or bitdepth combination*/
4060 state->error = checkColorValidity(info->color.colortype, info->color.bitdepth);
4061 if(state->error) return state->error;
4062 /*error: only compression method 0 is allowed in the specification*/
4063 if(info->compression_method != 0) CERROR_RETURN_ERROR(state->error, 32);
4064 /*error: only filter method 0 is allowed in the specification*/
4065 if(info->filter_method != 0) CERROR_RETURN_ERROR(state->error, 33);
4066 /*error: only interlace methods 0 and 1 exist in the specification*/
4067 if(info->interlace_method > 1) CERROR_RETURN_ERROR(state->error, 34);
4068
4069 if(!state->decoder.ignore_crc) {
4070 unsigned CRC = lodepng_read32bitInt(&in[29]);
4071 unsigned checksum = lodepng_crc32(&in[12], 17);
4072 if(CRC != checksum) {
4073 CERROR_RETURN_ERROR(state->error, 57); /*invalid CRC*/
4074 }
4075 }
4076
4077 return state->error;
4078}

2171 /*error: 256 * in[0] + in[1] must be a multiple of 31, the FCHECK value is supposed to be made that way*/
2172 return 24;
2173 }
2174
2175 CM = in[0] & 15;
2176 CINFO = (in[0] >> 4) & 15;
2177 /*FCHECK = in[1] & 31;*/ /*FCHECK is already tested above*/
2178 FDICT = (in[1] >> 5) & 1;
2179 /*FLEVEL = (in[1] >> 6) & 3;*/ /*FLEVEL is not used here*/
2180
2181 if(CM != 8 || CINFO > 7) {
2182 /*error: only compression method 8: inflate with sliding window of 32k is supported by the PNG spec*/
2183 return 25;
2184 }
2185 if(FDICT != 0) {
2186 /*error: the specification of PNG says about the zlib stream:
2187 "The additional flags shall not specify a preset dictionary."*/
2188 return 26;
2189 }
2190
2191 error = inflatev(out, in + 2, insize - 2, settings);
2192 if(error) return error;
2193
2194 if(!settings->ignore_adler32) {
2195 unsigned ADLER32 = lodepng_read32bitInt(&in[insize - 4]);
2196 unsigned checksum = adler32(out->data, (unsigned)(out->size));
2197 if(checksum != ADLER32) return 58; /*error, adler checksum not correct, data must be corrupted*/
2198 }
2199
2200 return 0; /*no error*/
2201}

4286 {
4287 /*
4288 This function converts the filtered-padded-interlaced data into pure 2D image buffer with the PNG's colortype.
4289 Steps:
4290 *) if no Adam7: 1) unfilter 2) remove padding bits (= possible extra bits per scanline if bpp < 8)
4291 *) if adam7: 1) 7x unfilter 2) 7x remove padding bits 3) Adam7_deinterlace
4292 NOTE: the in buffer will be overwritten with intermediate data!
4293 */
4294 unsigned bpp = lodepng_get_bpp(&info_png->color);
4295 if(bpp == 0) return 31; /*error: invalid colortype*/
4296
4297 if(info_png->interlace_method == 0) {
4298 if(bpp < 8 && w * bpp != ((w * bpp + 7u) / 8u) * 8u) {
4299 CERROR_TRY_RETURN(unfilter(in, in, w, h, bpp));
4300 removePaddingBits(out, in, w * bpp, ((w * bpp + 7u) / 8u) * 8u, h);
4301 }
4302 /*we can immediately filter into the out buffer, no other steps needed*/
4303 else CERROR_TRY_RETURN(unfilter(out, in, w, h, bpp));
4304 } else /*interlace_method is 1 (Adam7)*/ {
4305 unsigned passw[7], passh[7]; size_t filter_passstart[8], padded_passstart[8], passstart[8];
4306 unsigned i;
4307
4308 Adam7_getpassvalues(passw, passh, filter_passstart, padded_passstart, passstart, w, h, bpp);
4309
4310 for(i = 0; i != 7; ++i) {
4311 CERROR_TRY_RETURN(unfilter(&in[padded_passstart[i]], &in[filter_passstart[i]], passw[i], passh[i], bpp));
4312 /*TODO: possible efficiency improvement: if in this reduced image the bits fit nicely in 1 scanline,
4313 move bytes instead of bits or move not at all*/
4314 if(bpp < 8) {
4315 /*remove padding bits in scanlines; after this there still may be padding
4316 bits between the different reduced images: each reduced image still starts nicely at a byte*/
4317 removePaddingBits(&in[passstart[i]], &in[padded_passstart[i]], passw[i] * bpp,
4318 ((passw[i] * bpp + 7u) / 8u) * 8u, passh[i]);
4319 }
4320 }
4321
4322 Adam7_deinterlace(out, in, w, h, bpp);
4323 }

4325 return 0;

◆ removePaddingBits()

static void removePaddingBits ( unsigned char *  out,
const unsigned char *  in,
size_t  olinebits,
size_t  ilinebits,
unsigned  h 
)
static
4259 {
4260 /*
4261 After filtering there are still padding bits if scanlines have non multiple of 8 bit amounts. They need
4262 to be removed (except at last scanline of (Adam7-reduced) image) before working with pure image buffers
4263 for the Adam7 code, the color convert code and the output to the user.
4264 in and out are allowed to be the same buffer, in may also be higher but still overlapping; in must
4265 have >= ilinebits*h bits, out must have >= olinebits*h bits, olinebits must be <= ilinebits
4266 also used to move bits after earlier such operations happened, e.g. in a sequence of reduced images from Adam7
4267 only useful if (ilinebits - olinebits) is a value in the range 1..7
4268 */
4269 unsigned y;
4270 size_t diff = ilinebits - olinebits;
4271 size_t ibp = 0, obp = 0; /*input and output bit pointers*/
4272 for(y = 0; y < h; ++y) {
4273 size_t x;
4274 for(x = 0; x < olinebits; ++x) {
4275 unsigned char bit = readBitFromReversedStream(&ibp, in);
4276 setBitOfReversedStream(&obp, out, bit);
4277 }
4278 ibp += diff;
4279 }
4280}

◆ unfilter()

static unsigned unfilter ( unsigned char *  out,
const unsigned char *  in,
unsigned  w,
unsigned  h,
unsigned  bpp 
)
static
4177 {
4178 /*
4179 For PNG filter method 0
4180 this function unfilters a single image (e.g. without interlacing this is called once, with Adam7 seven times)
4181 out must have enough bytes allocated already, in must have the scanlines + 1 filtertype byte per scanline
4182 w and h are image dimensions or dimensions of reduced image, bpp is bits per pixel
4183 in and out are allowed to be the same memory address (but aren't the same size since in has the extra filter bytes)
4184 */
4185
4186 unsigned y;
4187 unsigned char* prevline = 0;
4188
4189 /*bytewidth is used for filtering, is 1 when bpp < 8, number of bytes per pixel otherwise*/
4190 size_t bytewidth = (bpp + 7u) / 8u;
4191 /*the width of a scanline in bytes, not including the filter type*/
4192 size_t linebytes = lodepng_get_raw_size_idat(w, 1, bpp) - 1u;
4193
4194 for(y = 0; y < h; ++y) {
4195 size_t outindex = linebytes * y;
4196 size_t inindex = (1 + linebytes) * y; /*the extra filterbyte added to each row*/
4197 unsigned char filterType = in[inindex];
4198
4199 CERROR_TRY_RETURN(unfilterScanline(&out[outindex], &in[inindex + 1], prevline, bytewidth, filterType, linebytes));
4200
4201 prevline = &out[outindex];
4202 }
4203
4204 return 0;
4205}

4083 For PNG filter method 0
4084 unfilter a PNG image scanline by scanline. when the pixels are smaller than 1 byte,
4085 the filter works byte per byte (bytewidth = 1)
4086 precon is the previous unfiltered scanline, recon the result, scanline the current one
4087 the incoming scanlines do NOT include the filtertype byte, that one is given in the parameter filterType instead
4088 recon and scanline MAY be the same memory address! precon must be disjoint.
